Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.95,0:00:03.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.07,0:00:06.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to go back\Nto your Landing Castle
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.74,0:00:09.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and find out where the real\NPrincess Asseylum is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.08,0:00:12.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.92,0:00:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because you want the same thing\Nas Princess Asseylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.51,0:00:21.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's one other thing that I\Nwant you to find out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.22,0:00:25.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What Slaine Troyard's objective is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.97,0:00:27.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.26,0:00:29.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.73,0:00:35.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you meet Princess Asseylum,\Nshow this to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.81,0:00:38.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She'll know that you are on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.41,0:00:49.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.76,0:02:27.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What happened after that, Harklight?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.13,0:02:30.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pacification of the Lake Victoria area
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.64,0:02:33.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,centered around the Landing Castle\Ntouchdown point is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.64,0:02:34.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.68,0:02:37.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The might of a united front\Nby multiple Orbital Knights
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.77,0:02:41.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,struck fear into more than the UFE, I'd wager.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.36,0:02:47.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that this success will have impressed\Nupon everyone the value of a leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.24,0:02:49.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because they never expected\Na difficult fight on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.36,0:02:52.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,not with the power of Aldnoah\Nat their disposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.83,0:02:55.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aldnoah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.04,0:03:03.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Saazbaum lamented our hierarchical\Nsociety based on Aldnoah activation rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.96,0:03:07.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He even believed it was a mistake to\Nlive on Mars in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.72,0:03:14.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because they had the power to do so, humans\Nmigrated to Mars and began the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.76,0:03:17.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum, Princess Lemrina...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.64,0:03:19.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both are victims of Aldnoah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.90,0:03:22.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That holds true for us, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.90,0:03:27.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But our days of being swallowed\Nby that power are at an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.32,0:03:30.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using the territory we gained\Nin this battle as a beachhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.70,0:03:33.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we will eventually expand our domain\Nacross the entire Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.58,0:03:38.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then, by combining the power of\NAldnoah with bountiful resources,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.04,0:03:39.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,we will build our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.84,0:03:46.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Repair status?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.38,0:03:48.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not good, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:51.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The wiring is fried, and it's taking\Na long time to replace it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.64,0:03:55.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A mission at a time like this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.26,0:03:59.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Deucalion is grounded,\Nso our Kataphraktoi platoons
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.35,0:04:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,will have to be transported via\Nlanding craft to the battle line.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.44,0:04:07.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our two platoons will attack the Landing Castle\Nfrom the north and cause a disturbance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.32,0:04:10.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and provide cover for the assault force\Nthat will attack from the southwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:15.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Commando unit" has a nice ring to it,\Nbut we're really just sacrificial pawns.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.45,0:04:18.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps Command has calculated that\Nthe odds are in their favor somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.54,0:04:22.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think those odds extend to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.37,0:04:23.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.79,0:04:27.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I suppose we need\Nto run our own set of numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.00,0:04:30.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kaizuka Jr.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.30,0:04:34.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can that fast thinking of yours do something\Nabout those damn Martians?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.72,0:04:36.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.51,0:04:41.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Elektris, which uses electricity as a weapon.\NAnd Skandia, which can turn invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.48,0:04:43.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both are formidable on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.31,0:04:46.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And as far as the Ortygia's\Nreplication ability goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.27,0:04:47.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have anywhere near enough data.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.69,0:04:50.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sparks, Dupes, and Houdini.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.53,0:04:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's like we're in a Sonny Chiba\Nmovie or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.90,0:04:56.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We know from observation\Nthat when the Ortygia splits,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.70,0:05:01.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it always splits from one into two,\Nnever into three or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.87,0:05:05.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When the second one appears, it's always\Nwithin a radius of 30 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.54,0:05:09.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much it splits, there's probably\Nonly one original that's piloted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.63,0:05:11.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The rest are fakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.17,0:05:14.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So our only option is to locate\Nand destroy the original.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.34,0:05:15.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But how do we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.89,0:05:20.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the only way is to mark the original\Nbefore it duplicates and track it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.22,0:05:25.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we put up a smoke screen, we can use trails\Nin the smoke to locate the Skandia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.35,0:05:27.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the lightning?\NDo you have any ideas for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.86,0:05:33.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One hit from that, and it'll blow\Nour electronics and actuators.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.07,0:05:36.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about insulators? You know, the stuff\Nthat doesn't conduct electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.03,0:05:40.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid?\NWhat are you, a grade-schooler?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.66,0:05:43.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I stupid?\NWhat's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.62,0:05:46.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Air already is an insulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.29,0:05:51.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to block electricity that's powerful\Nenough to punch through so much insulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.38,0:05:53.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what makes it really tricky
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.42,0:05:57.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is the fact that these tough bastards\Nare working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:06:00.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they're bad enough one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.10,0:06:02.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.35,0:06:03.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I might have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.56,0:06:06.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna use your eye again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.15,0:06:09.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:12.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always running a mutation code.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.98,0:06:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It gets more and more optimized over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.74,0:06:19.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Its predictive ability is\Neven better than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.28,0:06:21.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Calm, will you do a loadout change for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.79,0:06:24.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No problem. Just tell me what you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.37,0:06:27.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What I used up there. I need those.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.30,0:06:40.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Princess Lemrina, the invasion of Earth\Nis proceeding without incident.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.76,0:06:43.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I knew that you could do it, Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.31,0:06:46.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On a related note, perhaps\Nyou could say a few words{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.60,0:06:49.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to those Orbital Knights who\Ndistinguished themselves in battle?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.19,0:06:51.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Me," you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.44,0:06:54.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes. If Princess Asseylum were\Nto honor their achievements,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.82,0:06:57.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}it would win over more\NOrbital Knights to our side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.11,0:06:59.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Our" side?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.28,0:07:01.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes, Princess Lemrina.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.16,0:07:04.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.70,0:07:08.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, Slaine,\Nwhat is my sister's condition?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.79,0:07:12.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The reports say that she is\Nstill in critical condition.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.71,0:07:13.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.71,0:07:17.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For now, all we can do is have faith in the\Nmedical staff and entrust her to their care.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.92,0:07:21.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, let's pray for a quick recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.76,0:07:24.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't dwell on it\Ntoo much either, Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.01,0:07:28.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you for your kind words.\NExcuse me, but I must go.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.40,0:07:33.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:44.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Clydesdale Leader to all units!\NAll units, spread out!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.87,0:07:51.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mustang Leader to Mustang 00.\NNao, what's their position?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.29,0:07:52.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Preliminary results are in.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:55.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sending coordinates and timing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.21,0:07:59.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang 11, 22. Move out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.51,0:08:00.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Roger.\N- Roger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.90,0:08:14.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ortygia Master is our first target.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.52,0:08:17.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Attack simultaneously and destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.36,0:08:19.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sorraia Platoon, straight ahead!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.40,0:08:21.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotland Platoon, swing around to the west!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.78,0:08:23.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sorraia Platoon, acknowledged.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.62,0:08:25.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gotland Platoon, acknowledged!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.49,0:08:27.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Master is the third from the right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.00,0:08:30.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Commence attack!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.04,0:08:39.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You thought you had the original? Guess again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.47,0:08:43.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, Orga, will deal with\Nthe main enemy force.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.55,0:08:50.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nonius Platoon, Pleven Platoon, launch\Nfocused attack on the Skandia and destroy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.81,0:08:51.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Smoke grenades, fire.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.69,0:09:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Spotted him! Over there!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.13,0:09:03.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Fire, fire, fire, fire!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.20,0:09:09.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Up to the same tricks again?\NWhat an unimaginative bunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.16,0:09:12.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Count Sebring?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.21,0:09:15.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have a little fun\Nwith them, Count Raffia!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.75,0:09:21.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The smoke screen vanished?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.92,0:09:24.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Colloids are absorbed by ions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:28.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is another way to use electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.60,0:09:34.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A lightning attack from Invisibility?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.56,0:09:38.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When one dies in battle, it ought to be\Na beautiful death, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.28,0:09:43.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming that you are true\NKataphraktos operators.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.49,0:09:47.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Main force and assault units\Nboth seem to be having trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.45,0:09:51.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that Lightning and Invisibility\Nare working together.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.00,0:09:54.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang 00, what's your status?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.04,0:09:55.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Data collected!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.04,0:10:00.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The smoke screen negation and expanded\Ninvisibility field were unexpected, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.00,0:10:01.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you compensate?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.59,0:10:03.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll manage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.05,0:10:05.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.38,0:10:10.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After I lost consciousness, the war\Nhas gone on for nearly two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.85,0:10:12.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milady.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.39,0:10:13.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And it is Slaine who...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.14,0:10:18.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.15,0:10:23.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.99,0:10:25.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To see Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.65,0:10:28.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And to learn the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.37,0:10:29.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.71,0:10:37.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You–
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.21,0:10:39.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.59,0:10:46.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why... must you always stand in my way?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.22,0:10:48.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who are...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.01,0:10:50.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.51,0:10:51.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.40,0:11:04.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Using tactical data link to analyze\Nenemy behavior multidimensionally
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and deduce enemy's\Nhabits in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.78,0:11:12.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will deploy friendlies in positions vulnerable\Nto enemies' preferred attack patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.37,0:11:14.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and prompt them to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:17.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whether the analysis will be\Ncomplete in time, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:20.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sending most recent data. Take positions!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.75,0:11:21.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}- Roger.\N- Roger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.75,0:11:23.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Roger here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.76,0:11:30.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's probably right-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.05,0:11:34.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He moves counter-clockwise to make it\Neasier to attack enemies to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.27,0:11:38.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don't like being bait...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.73,0:11:39.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.85,0:11:42.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's circling around behind you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.31,0:11:44.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To keep from giving away his position,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.40,0:11:46.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he should stop his lightning attack and then,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.03,0:11:50.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}once he's behind his target, he'll momentarily\Ncome to a stop and take careful aim.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.24,0:11:54.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yuki, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.49,0:11:56.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is he really there?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.08,0:12:01.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Found him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.04,0:12:02.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.13,0:12:05.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is Mustang Leader, target spotted!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.13,0:12:07.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mustang 00, launching.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.88,0:12:10.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Mustang 00! Dropping!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.64,0:12:22.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Skandia's leg...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.31,0:12:24.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It can't support the Elektris' weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.07,0:12:26.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Disengage linkup!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.11,0:12:28.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will handle this! Get clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.44,0:12:30.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Targets confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.90,0:12:31.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,#9, fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.79,0:12:42.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I told you, that won't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.75,0:12:43.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How about these rounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.80,0:12:48.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.05,0:12:51.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Electricity flows from high\Npotential to low potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.51,0:12:54.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your lightning won't strike an object with\Nthe same electrical potential as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.89,0:12:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's to keep you from\Nbeing struck yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.02,0:13:01.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have a taste of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.10,0:13:06.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late.\NI'm the same potential as you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.23,0:13:12.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...\NThis is the orange one I've heard about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.07,0:13:15.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Count Sebring!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.82,0:13:18.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am sending assistance! Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.71,0:13:24.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inaho!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.71,0:13:25.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Smoke grenades!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.01,0:13:32.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.14,0:13:36.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.22,0:13:44.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Curse you, you've killed my comrades...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.52,0:13:45.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You will pay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.03,0:13:57.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you okay, Nao?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.45,0:13:59.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Thanks, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.37,0:14:01.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}9 o'clock!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.92,0:14:14.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here they come! Pick them off!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.57,0:14:36.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You wished to see me, Princess Lemrina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.41,0:14:39.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.08,0:14:41.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.08,0:14:50.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum... My sister...\NShe has already woken up, hasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.05,0:14:57.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I always knew that I would have\Nto tell you eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.43,0:15:00.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind explaining yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.05,0:15:04.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum is\Nnot quite herself yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.60,0:15:11.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I needed to have you continue to\Nportray her until she recovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.44,0:15:13.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In order to create a new world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.69,0:15:16.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A new world?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.44,0:15:19.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a world free of worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.99,0:15:25.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A world of everlasting peace,\None without conflict and without sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.41,0:15:28.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And who will rule this world?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.29,0:15:32.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her Highness Asseylum Vers Allusia, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.04,0:15:36.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe that my sister\Nwants such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.72,0:15:38.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that she does not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.13,0:15:42.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is exactly why I will make it\Na reality and present it to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.93,0:15:52.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness, do you know\Nwhy wars break out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.73,0:15:56.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They are a means of negotiation\Nbetween states.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.99,0:16:01.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. Wars break out because\N there is someone to fight against.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.49,0:16:07.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To eliminate war, there are two options:\NInvade and assimilate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,or utterly exterminate one's adversary\Nso that only you remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.50,0:16:14.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mankind's history\Nis a history of conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.55,0:16:21.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The very instant that Mars split off\Nfrom Earth, war was inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.64,0:16:28.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... Even if I had not,\Nsomeone else eventually would have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.77,0:16:33.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.65,0:16:40.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are no longer\Nthe Slaine I once knew, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.75,0:16:56.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.38,0:17:00.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I told her everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.09,0:17:07.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the name of Asseylum Vers Allusia,\NPrincess Royal of the Vers Empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.18,0:17:14.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I order Count Slaine Saazbaum Troyard\Nto immediately cease all hostilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.61,0:17:22.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we just needed\Nto take out the master!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:25.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Which is the real one?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.45,0:17:27.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The one we marked wasn't the original!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.24,0:17:29.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where's it hiding?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.08,0:17:33.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that one of them would be\Nthe real one, but maybe I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.25,0:17:35.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.54,0:17:39.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My analysis of the duplicates\Nturned up something interesting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.13,0:17:42.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the instant that they manifest, the\Nmaster's state is perfectly preserved,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.84,0:17:45.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}everything from its orientation\Nto its energy state.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.80,0:17:47.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.18,0:17:51.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Maybe he's using quantum teleportation\Nto create copies of himself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.89,0:17:55.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Except the original is left intact\Ninstead of being destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.81,0:17:57.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,effectively creating a duplicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.19,0:17:59.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Again, meaning what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.19,0:18:00.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It means that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.99,0:18:04.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...they're all the real one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.99,0:18:12.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slave all Kataphraktoi platoon\Ntargeting and triggers to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.29,0:18:14.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Send request to company command post.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:15.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.25,0:18:19.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Inputting coordinates and vectors\Nfor all Ortygias...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.63,0:18:21.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How many more is\Nhe gonna make?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.13,0:18:23.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Any time now, Kaizuka Jr.!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.17,0:18:24.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Targets are multiplying.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.38,0:18:26.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I need more time to update.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.30,0:18:30.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If it's not one thing, it's another!\NOur ammo won't last forever!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.31,0:18:33.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tactical data link, synchronized.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.85,0:18:38.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaving all UFE Kataphraktoi targeting\Nto centralized control.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.02,0:18:41.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nao, how much longer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.11,0:18:45.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll only get one chance.\NIf they're all real...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.07,0:18:50.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All targets locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.87,0:18:51.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:12.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.81,0:19:18.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they're all real, we need to destroy\Nthem all at the same time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.19,0:19:20.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Enemy Kataphraktoi eliminated.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.15,0:19:22.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You did it, Inaho!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.94,0:19:25.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah. I'm glad it worked.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.49,0:19:27.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I couldn't have done it without you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.37,0:19:33.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.74,0:19:37.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please, put an end to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.37,0:19:41.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.29,0:19:44.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot obey your order.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.13,0:19:50.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You see, I am no longer a citizen\Nof the Vers Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.97,0:19:53.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am terribly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.47,0:19:56.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must take you both into custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.39,0:19:59.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, message from General Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.81,0:20:00.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have about two minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.85,0:20:04.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,until the laser communications satellite\Ndips below the horizon, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.82,0:20:08.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That little? Put it on speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.95,0:20:12.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is Darzana Magbaredge,\Ncaptain of the Deucalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.49,0:20:14.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is Vice Admiral Eelis Hakkinen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.53,0:20:18.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was a brilliant operation.\NRetrofit progress status?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.91,0:20:20.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Almost finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.54,0:20:26.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's good to hear. It's equipment that the\NDeucalion will need on her new mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:29.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A mission in the Satellite Belt, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.09,0:20:29.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.97,0:20:32.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be going even higher this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.84,0:20:34.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You will be briefed later.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.64,0:20:38.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Transmission ended.\NThe laser's gain has dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.39,0:20:41.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Comms satellite is leaving line of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.98,0:20:44.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His way of saying he won't\Ntake no for an answer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.44,0:20:46.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like this is going\Nto be a large battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.82,0:20:48.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.61,0:20:53.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He thinks he can use us however he wants just\Nbecause the Deucalion has an Aldnoah drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.78,0:20:55.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A space loadout, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.33,0:20:57.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A catapult module...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.21,0:21:06.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.54,0:21:07.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.42,0:21:10.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The princesses have been made\Ncomfortable in their quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.72,0:21:11.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:16.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if they do not understand what you are trying\Nto accomplish, Milord, I'm sure that one day–
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.43,0:21:17.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.64,0:21:20.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whether or not I can get them\Nto understand is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.27,0:21:24.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Milord Slaine, a spaceship\Nis approaching the base.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.73,0:21:26.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is requesting permission to dock.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.94,0:21:28.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A spaceship?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.32,0:21:30.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is a visitor from the Vers homeworld.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.08,0:21:40.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.54,0:21:44.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The blue planet where\Nmy father lies interred...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.58,0:21:46.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Count Cruhteo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.67,0:21:48.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.34,0:21:52.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I still find it awkward to be\Naddressed by my father's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.17,0:21:54.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please call me Cronkine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.09,0:21:57.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish, Milord.\NCount Cronkine, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.51,0:22:02.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what will he\Nbe like, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.56,0:22:06.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go meet the son of Dr. Troyard.
